Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Located on the corner of Lindsay Street and Academy Road, this religious assembly structure was originally constructed in 1957 with an addition in 1984. The existing layout lends itself to a potential office or multi-family conversion. The building has been very meticulously maintained and extremely well-managed. It has received numerous upgrades in recent years including new basement windows, basement floor and weeping tile installed in 2020, a new hot water tank in 2019 and 4 new furnaces in 2009. There is an excellent power supply of 400 amps. The main chapel has a seating capacity of ~175-200 people and can open up to the gymnasium/auditorium for overflow seating. There are currently multi-user washrooms on the main and upper floors.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Prominent Presence on the Academy Retail Strip

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 431 Kensington Street is a perfect owner/user opportunity for the professional services supplier who wants all of the amenities that the Polo Park retail node has to offer. The beautifully finished±3,000 sq. ft. office space includes a mix of private offices, multiple meeting rooms, open area, reception and a shower for staff, while the ±1,000 sq. ft. warehouse is clean and heated with grade level overhead door access. Additionally, 431 Kensington provides the new owner/occupier with indoor cold storage and a large fenced compound to provide additional parking or secured storage area.
